# gstack Skills

gstack provides specialized AI workflows. When a user request matches a skill, read and follow its SKILL.md file.

## Skill Directory

All skills are located at: `gstack/[skill-name]/SKILL.md`

## Quick Reference

| Trigger | Skill | Read This File |
|---|----|----|
| `/qa [url]` or "test the site" | QA Testing | `gstack/qa/SKILL.md` |
| `/review` or "review my code" | Code Review | `gstack/review/SKILL.md` |
| `/ship` or "push this" | Ship & PR | `gstack/ship/SKILL.md` |
| `/investigate` or "why is this broken" | Debug | `gstack/investigate/SKILL.md` |
| `/browse` or "open [url]" | Headless Browser | `gstack/browse/SKILL.md` |
| `/office-hours` or "is this worth building" | Product Ideation | `gstack/office-hours/SKILL.md` |
| `/design-review` | Visual Design Audit | `gstack/design-review/SKILL.md` |
| `/cso` | Security Audit | `gstack/cso/SKILL.md` |
| `/plan-eng-review` | Architecture Review | `gstack/plan-eng-review/SKILL.md` |
| `/plan-ceo-review` | Strategy Review | `gstack/plan-ceo-review/SKILL.md` |
| `/retro` | Weekly Retrospective | `gstack/retro/SKILL.md` |

## How to Invoke

When you see a trigger phrase or slash command:

1. Read the corresponding SKILL.md file from the gstack directory
2. Follow the instructions in that file exactly
3. Use the skill's structured workflow instead of answering ad-hoc

## Browse Tool

The `/browse` skill provides a headless browser. After setup, use:

```bash
# Set the browse binary path
B=gstack/browse/dist/browse

# Common commands
$B goto https://example.com    # Navigate
$B snapshot -i                 # See interactive elements
$B click @e3                   # Click element by ref
$B screenshot /tmp/shot.png    # Take screenshot
$B text                        # Get page text
```

## Routing Rules

- Bugs, errors, "why broken" → `/investigate`
- Ship, deploy, PR → `/ship`
- Test site, QA, find bugs → `/qa`
- Review code, check diff → `/review`
- Product ideas, brainstorming → `/office-hours`
- Visual polish, design audit → `/design-review`
- Security concerns → `/cso`
